      "content": "There was never a consensus that nonviolence was the *only* way; many groups like the Black Panther Party and the Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee actively debated and sometimes rejected that approach. While mainstream history books often focus on the nonviolent wing, the movement was actually a dynamic coalition where radical, violent, and moderate factions constantly challenged each other to drive change. Ignoring these diverse strategies gives an incomplete picture of how the movement evolved and why so many different tactics were necessary.",
